1 2. "New direct job" shall include full-time-equivalent
2 employment in this state of remote workers who are employed by an
3 establishment other than the proxy establishment which has qualified
4 to receive incentive payments for attracting remote workers to the
5 state. Such jobs held by remote workers did not exist in this state
6 prior to the date of approval by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce
7 of the application of the proxy establishment. A job shall be
8 deemed to exist in this state prior to approval of an application if
9 the activities and functions for which the particular job exists
10 have been ongoing at any time within six (6) months prior to such
11 approval;
12 3. "Proxy establishment" means:
13 a. a public trust which:
14 (1) is organized and existing under Section 176 of
15 Title 60 of the Oklahoma Statutes for the benefit
16 of a geographic area which includes a city or
17 county or some combination thereof, and
18 (2) benefits a geographic area where new direct jobs
19 which meet the requirements of the Oklahoma
20 Remote Quality Jobs Incentive Act are created by
21 an establishment, other than the proxy
22 establishment, or
23 b. an establishment which facilitates the attraction of
24 remote workers to the State of Oklahoma;
