1 4. "Remote worker" refers to a work flexibility arrangement
2 under which an employee performs the duties and responsibilities of
3 such employee's position, and other authorized activities, from an
4 approved work site other than the location from which the employee
5 would otherwise work, which shall not be located within the physical
6 boundaries of the State of Oklahoma. The remote worker should not
7 have lived in the State of Oklahoma in the previous twelve (12)
8 months;
9 5. "Estimated direct state benefits" means the tax revenues
10 projected by the Department to accrue to the state as a result of
11 new direct jobs;
12 6. "Estimated direct state costs" means the costs projected by
13 the Department to accrue to the state as a result of new direct
14 jobs. Such costs shall include, but not be limited to:
15 a. the costs of education of new state resident children,
16 b. the costs of public health, public safety and
17 transportation services to be provided to new state
18 residents,
19 c. the costs of other state services to be provided to
20 new state residents, and
21 d. the costs of other state services;
22 7. "Estimated net direct state benefits" means the estimated
23 direct state benefits less the estimated direct state costs; and
24
