1 8. "Net benefit rate" means the estimated net direct state
2 benefits computed as a percentage of gross payroll, and shall not
3 exceed five percent (5%).
4 B. A proxy establishment shall be required to obtain from
5 remote workers proof of basic health benefits plans for the
6 individuals it includes in an application. The proxy establishment
7 shall submit the information to the Oklahoma Department of Commerce
8 and shall ensure that the basic health benefits plans consist of the
9 following elements or elements substantially equivalent thereto:
10 1. Not more than fifty percent (50%) of the premium shall be
11 paid by the employee;
12 2. Coverage for basic hospital care;
13 3. Coverage for physician care;
14 4. Coverage for mental health care;
15 5. Coverage for substance abuse treatment;
16 6. Coverage for prescription drugs; and
17 7. Coverage for prenatal care.
18 provide coverage where not more than fifty percent (50%) of the
19 premium shall be paid by the employee; however, services provided by
20 an Employee Assistance Plan (EAP) are not sufficient to meet this
21 definition.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
